The last time I checked, I think it supports arbitrary X (divisible by 8 ) and Y (all integers) resolutions of up to 512x256 and pixel clocks corresponding to approximately 512, 320, and 256 pixels visible onscreen. <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/TurboGrafx-16#Display" class="postlink">Wikipedia</a><br /><br />edit: killed the accidental smiley<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3512">lidnariq</a> — Fri Aug 31, 2012 6:52 pm</p><hr />
